INTRODUCTION
============

Hallo! Welcome to the Kakao Linux tutorial.

You can navigate the tutorial using the up and down arrow keys or the
page up and page down keys.

You can press the 'q' key at any time to exit the tutorial.

This is a very basic tutorial designed to be useful to users with any level
of experience using Linux, or computers in general.

After exiting the tutorial, you can enter commands at the command prompt,
which is displayed as '$'.

BASICS
======

List files in the current directory:

 $ ls

Print the name of the current directory:

 $ pwd

Make a directory:

 $ mkdir mydir

Change to a different directory:

 $ cd mydir

Change to the parent directory:

 $ cd ..

Create an empty file:

 $ touch myfile

Remove a file:

 $ rm myfile

TEXT EDITING
============

Kakao provides multiple options for editing text.

 NANO
 ----

 $ nano

 To edit an existing file, type the filename after the command:

 $ nano myfile.txt

 VI
 --

 $ vi

 After starting vi, type ':q' and press enter to quit.

PROGRAMMING
===========

Lisp:

 $ tinyscheme
 ts> (+ 1 2 3)

Python:

 $ micropython
 >>> a = 5
 >>> print(a*2)

C:

 $ echo "#include <tcclib.h>" > hello.c
 $ echo "int main() { printf(\"Hello world\!\n\"); return 0; }" >> hello.c
 $ tcc -o hello hello.c
 $ ./hello


THINGS TO DO
============

Read a book:

 $ ark search pg alice
 $ ark read pg 34

Read an encyclopedia article:

 $ ark search wp morse
 $ ark read wp 5873

View an image:

 $ fbv /opt/ark/gutenberg/cia/maps/gm-map.gif

Communicate with a USB-UART device:

 $ screen /dev/ttyUSB0 115200		# press CTRL-A K to exit


NETWORKING
==========

If your computer has built-in Ethernet or you have a compatible USB Ethernet or
WiFi adapter, you can connect to your local network and the Internet.

Connect to Machdyne BBS:

 $ bbs
